question_text: Which two symptoms are most likely caused by a spooler crash in Windows? (Select two)
answer_options: Jobs appear in the queue but don’t print
The print spooler service is stopped
The ink level monitor shows inaccurate data
Network print jobs are automatically rerouted
correct_answer: Jobs appear in the queue but don’t print
The print spooler service is stopped
explanation: When the spooler crashes, jobs accumulate in the queue and the spooler service is either paused or completely stopped.
